The governorship campaign posters of Barr. Natasha Akpoti on the platform of Social Democratic Party (SDP) have resurfaced in some strategic parts of Lokoja, the Kogi State capital, ahead of the forthcoming election. Daily Trust observed yesterday that supporters of Natasha had pasted her campaign posters in locations such as Zenith Bank Junction, Kogi Circle Roundabout and NTA Roundabout, amongst others. Natasha, who emerged governorship candidate of SDP for the November governorship election, was however disqualified by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on the ground that her running mate was under aged. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY She protested against the decision of INEC and has since approached a court in Abuja to seek redress. I’m still in the race — Natasha Akpoti SDP gets candidate for Kogi gov’ship Kogi Guber: Natasha thrown out after issuing quit notice to Gov Bello